1. What is HTML and the purpose of using HTML?
    - HTML describes the structure of a web page. It tells the browser how to display content on a page.
2. What is head and body tags used for in HTML documents?
    - The invisible part of the HTML document goes into <head></head> tag
        - Page title
        - Links to CSS
    - The visible part of the HTML document goes into <body></body> tag
        - Headings
        - Paragraphs
        - Images
        - Tables
        - Lists
        - etc.
3. What are tags and elements in an HTML document?
    - Everything that we see on a web page is web element
    - Tag is basically considered as container in HTML
4. What is the difference between tags and attributes?
    - HTML elements can have many attributes
        - This can include style attribute with HTML elements to define elements’ color, font, size, background color, alignment, etc
5. Please list the HTML tags you know and explain them shortly.
    <html> … </html> — The root element.
    <head> … </head> — The document head.
    <title> … </title> — The page title.
    <body> … </body> — The page's content.
    <h1> … </h1> — A section heading.
    <p> … </p> — A paragraph.
    <a> … </a> — A link.
    <img> — An image
